        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "马尔科夫模型在NLP中的应用举例",
        "bbox": [
            191,
            218,
            811,
            296
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "images/4637d80b7f157642f8dceea781cdbd182050ea01458a0b3c55565d8ac49b511a.jpg",
        "text": "$$\nS = \\{ \\mathbf { s } _ { 1 } = n , \\mathbf { s } _ { 2 } = \\nu , \\mathbf { s } _ { 3 } = a \\}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            369,
            314,
            587,
            361
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "images/382ac113a9580e89aeb3f2237314dae4e847517cbfbc71cd790da906480fb174.jpg",
        "text": "$$\n\\overset { n } { \\underset { { A = \\left( \\mathbf { a } _ { i j } \\right) = \\nu } } { \\sum } } \\overset { n } { \\underset { { \\nu } } { \\sum } } \\overset { \\nu } { \\underset { { \\left( \\mathbf { 0 . 3 } \\right. \\begin{array} { l } { { 0 . 5 } } \\end{array} } } { \\sum } } 0 . 2 \n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            337,
            392,
            565,
            574
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "images/3a2799a030477b4a002002e4139acb7ff052334ca53756eef2f7451d4fdc1f29.jpg",
        "text": "$$\n\\pi = \\{ \\pi _ { \\mathrm { i } } \\} = { \\begin{array} { c c c } { n } & { \\quad \\nu } & { \\quad a } \\\\ { [ \\phantom { { \\ e q e m e m } } 0 . 6 } & { 0 . 2 } & { \\quad 0 . 2 } \\end{array} ] }\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            337,
            611,
            590,
            700
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "img_path": "images/af12fef5132134afb05d63723929e4450636f7ad8984932c1c64519869e9091c.jpg",
        "text": "$$\n\\begin{array} { r l } & { P ( q _ { 1 } = n , q _ { 2 } = \\nu , q _ { 3 } = a , q _ { 4 } = n ) } \\\\ & { = P ( q _ { 1 } = n ) \\times P ( q _ { 2 } = \\nu \\mid q _ { 1 } = n ) \\times P ( q _ { 3 } = a \\mid q _ { 2 } = \\nu ) \\times P ( q _ { 4 } = n \\mid q _ { 3 } = a ) } \\\\ & { = 0 . 6 \\times 0 . 5 \\times 0 . 2 \\times 0 . 4 } \\\\ & { = 0 . 0 2 4 } \\end{array}\n$$",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "bbox": [
            311,
            742,
            835,
            942
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
